						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1349 (1427 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Built in at places. Seems to refer to an endowment of land for a grove (<hi rend="italic">tōppu</hi>) after excluding from it the <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> and <hi rend="italic">bhaṭṭa-vṛitt</hi> portions. The donor whose name is lost appears to be a <hi rend="italic">śāttāda-Śrīvaishṇava</hi> hailing from Pratāpagiri in Uttara-dēśa. The details of date are mutilated but for the years <hi rend="bold">Parābhava (expired) and Plavaṅga (current) and the</hi> <hi rend="italic">nakshatra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Anurādhā</hi> and are thus insufficient for verification. <hi rend="bold">But the cyclic year Plavaṅga —(Śaka 1349)</hi> falling in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya (II 1422-1446 A.D.)</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1427 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
